HEADWORD: Semiologioal
<hw>Se`mi*o*log"io*al</hw> }</mhw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining
to the science of signs, or the systematic use of signs; <as>as, a
<ex>semeiological</ex> classification of the signs or symptoms of
disease; a <ex>semeiological</ex> arrangement of signs used as
signals.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

